- pipenv is a way to create a virtual env to develop an application with python and be able to recreate it exactly with the same package, same version etc..
- It permits to run simultenously on the same system different versions of python and of package. It's an isolated environmeement
- Anaconda is more than that
- one can think of it to be the matlab of data science and ML and AI
- miniconda install is only the "conda" command without packages
- this permits to download after through the conda command the needed packages only
- anaconda has conda + tons of pre installed packages.
- it also work with virtual environment
- the best way to think of it is matlab like with data processing packages env where python is the programming language of this env



